.TH "skb_gso_validate_network_len" 9 "skb_gso_validate_network_len" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
skb_gso_validate_network_len \- Will a split GSO skb fit into a given MTU?
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" skb_gso_validate_network_len
.BI "(const struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mtu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "skb" 12
GSO skb
.IP "mtu" 12
MTU to validate against
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
skb_gso_validate_network_len validates if a given skb will fit a
wanted MTU once split. It considers L3 headers, L4 headers, and the
payload.
